# Gitleaks Ignore File
# Reduces false positives from UI elements and theme files

# Shopify theme files contain HTML password form elements (not credentials)
themes/hotrodan-live/**/*.liquid
themes/hotrodan-live/locales/*.json
themes/hotrodan-live/locales/*.schema.json

# Theme assets contain UI strings that may trigger false positives
themes/**/assets/**/*.js
themes/**/assets/**/*.css

# Test files may contain example/mock credentials
tests/**/*.spec.ts
tests/**/*test*.ts

# Documentation may reference credential patterns as examples
docs/**/example*.md
docs/**/template*.md

# Package lock files contain package hashes that trigger false positives
package-lock.json
pnpm-lock.yaml
yarn.lock

# Build artifacts and generated files
dist/**
build/**
.next/**
coverage/**

# Git files themselves
.git/**

# Note: Actual secrets should NEVER be in git
# Use vault/ directory with 600 permissions for real credentials
# Reference credentials as environment variables: $VAR_NAME or ${VAR_NAME}
# Or use [REDACTED] placeholders in documentation

